A '''mobility kill''' (or '''M-kill''') in [[armoured warfare]] refers to damage inflicted by a weapon on a vehicle that immobizes it, but does not totally destroy it, leaving the vehicle's crew able to use its weapons.  Typically this term is used to refer to [[tank]]s and other [[armoured fighting vehicle]]s that have their engines, tracks, or running gear damaged.  Because of the mobile nature of modern warfare, such a vehicle is often effectively useless on the battlefield, but it may be salvaged, repaired, and brought back into action quickly.

